text: Catawba is an unincorporated community in Caldwell County, in the U.S. state of Missouri. ==History== Catawba was laid out in 1884, and named for a grove of catalpa trees near the original town site. A post office called Catawba was established in 1872, and remained in operation until 1905. ==References== Category:Unincorporated communities in Caldwell County, Missouri Category:1872 establishments in Missouri Category:Unincorporated communities in Missouri
title: Catawba, Missouri
